INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (7, 'TECH-74', 'decision_log', '| Date | Decision | Rationale | Alternatives considered |
|------|----------|-----------|------------------------|
| 2026-04-06 | Single issue for **both** commands | Shared **bridge** contract, one **MCP** / **verify** pass, one closeout. | Split **TECH-** per command — rejected for overhead. |
| 2026-04-06 | Reuse **`agent_bridge_job`** | Matches glossary **IDE agent bridge** and shipped **Phase 1**. | New table or HTTP **Phase 2** — out of scope. |
| 2026-04-06 | **`get_console_logs`** / **`capture_screenshot`** are **`unity_bridge_command`** **`kind`** values | **territory-ia** keeps one **registerTool** entry (**`unity_bridge_command`**) + **`unity_bridge_get`**; discovery text lists all **`kind`** values. Matches [`docs/unity-ide-agent-bridge-analysis.md`](../../docs/unity-ide-agent-bridge-analysis.md) §4.3 command names. | Separate top-level **`registerTool("get_console_logs")`** (sugar) — defer unless product requires duplicate tool names in the MCP manifest. [`docs/unity-ide-agent-bridge-analysis.md`](../../docs/unity-ide-agent-bridge-analysis.md) §5.1 **`unity_get_logs`** / **`unity_capture_screenshot`** remain **charter aliases** only unless a future issue adds thin wrappers. |
| 2026-04-06 | **`params`** live under **`request` jsonb** | **dequeue** already returns **`request_json`**; **Unity** must start parsing it for non-default kinds. | Duplicate params in **SQL** columns — rejected; keep **0008** schema. |
| 2026-04-07 | **`log_lines`** + **`AgentBridgeLogLineDto`** | Single array on **`unity_agent_bridge_response`**; **Unity** **`JsonUtility`** + **TS** optional field. | Nested **`details`** object — rejected for **JsonUtility** friction. |
| 2026-04-07 | **Console buffer** cleared on **script domain reload** | **`AssemblyReloadEvents.beforeAssemblyReload`**; predictable baseline for **`since_utc`**. | Persist across reload — rejected (stale noise). |
| 2026-04-07 | **`camera`** = **GameObject.name** exact match | **`Object.FindObjectsOfType`** on **Camera** (one-shot, not per-frame). | Hierarchy path — deferred. |
| 2026-04-07 | Full-game **`ScreenCapture`** completes via **`EditorApplication.delayCall`** | **Unity** writes PNG at end of frame; job **`TryCompleteSuccess`** runs next tick. | Synchronous **`File.Exists`** — unreliable immediately after **`CaptureScreenshot`**. |
| 2026-04-07 | **`verify-mcp`** accepts **`unity_bridge_command`** **success** | Dev machines with **DB** + **Unity** return **`unity_agent_bridge_response`**; CI without them still accept **timeout** / **db_unconfigured** / **db_error**. | Success-only CI — impossible without **Unity**. |
| 2026-04-07 | Out-of-range **`max_lines`** | **MCP** host **JSON Schema** (from **Zod**) rejects before handler; **`unityBridgeCommandInputSchema`** unit test covers **`safeParse`**. | **`verify-mcp`** **`invalid_input`** call — removed (non-JSON **MCP error** on some hosts). |', '{extend,shipped,bridge,glossary,postgres,agent_bridge_job,unity,agentbridgecommandrunner,territory-ia,unity_bridge_command,unity_bridge_get,request,console,excerpts,play,agent,agents,mode,screenshots,issue,bundles,get_console_logs,capture_screenshot,kind,values,existing,decision,naming,docs/unity-ide-agent-bridge-analysis,/docs/unity-ide-agent-bridge-analysis,sibling,tech-59}', '.cursor/projects/TECH-74.md', '2026-04-06 21:51:13.476608-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (8, 'TECH-74', 'lessons_learned', '- **`ScreenCapture.CaptureScreenshot`** needs a short delay before **`File.Exists`**; **`EditorApplication.delayCall`** is unreliable during **Play Mode**, so **`AgentBridgeCommandRunner`** polls **`EditorApplication.update`** until the file exists or a **wall-clock** budget (**15s**) elapses (frame counts alone misalign with MCP **`timeout_ms`** when the Editor update rate drops). **`unity_bridge_command`** **`timeout_ms`** default and max **30s**.
- **`JsonUtility`** cannot bind **`params`** (C# keyword); rewrite **`"params":`** → **`"bridge_params":`** before **`FromJson`**.
- Manual **`unity_bridge_command`** smoke: `kind: "get_console_logs"` and `kind: "capture_screenshot"` (Play Mode) from **Cursor** or root script invoking **`runUnityBridgeCommand`**.', '{extend,shipped,bridge,glossary,postgres,agent_bridge_job,unity,agentbridgecommandrunner,territory-ia,unity_bridge_command,unity_bridge_get,request,console,excerpts,play,agent,agents,mode,screenshots,issue,bundles,get_console_logs,capture_screenshot,kind,values,existing,decision,naming,docs/unity-ide-agent-bridge-analysis,/docs/unity-ide-agent-bridge-analysis,sibling,tech-59}', '.cursor/projects/TECH-74.md', '2026-04-06 21:51:13.499548-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (9, 'TECH-194', 'decision_log', '- **Route caching** — `export const dynamic = ''force-static''` per Next 16.2.3 route-handler [caching guide](../../node_modules/next/dist/docs/01-app/01-getting-started/15-route-handlers.md#caching). Fs scan deterministic → prerender at build. Revalidate on next `next build` (new devlog post → rebuild triggers refresh via CI).
- **RFC-822 pubDate** — `new Date(''YYYY-MM-DD'').toUTCString()` native output matches RFC-822 shape (`Wed, 15 Apr 2026 00:00:00 GMT`) accepted by W3C feed validator.
- **Absolute URLs** — `getBaseUrl()` from `web/lib/site/base-url.ts` for `<link>` + `<guid isPermaLink="true">`. Consistent w/ `web/app/sitemap.ts` precedent.
- **XML escape** — inline 5-char escape helper (`&` → `&amp;`, `<` → `&lt;`, `>` → `&gt;`, `"` → `&quot;`, `''` → `&apos;`). No template lib to keep surface minimal.
- **Validator snapshot** — record URL + PASS/warnings after Phase 3 manual check here.
- **Autodiscovery `<link rel="alternate">`** — deferred to **TECH-195** (touches `web/app/layout.tsx` `<head>`).', '{author,next,router,route,handler,returns,version,channel,enumerating,latest,devlog,posts,item,entries,title,web/app/feed,xml/route,/node_modules/next/dist/docs/01-app/01-getting-started/15-route-handlers,/channel,/rss,link,description,excerpt,pubdate,rfc-822,guid,response,header,content-type,application/rss,charset,utf-8}', 'ia/projects/TECH-194-web-rss-feed-route.md', '2026-04-15 12:25:43.833964-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
