| 2026-04-18 | Audit is separate task from wiring tasks | Single-responsibility keeps wiring PR small and audit PR focused; also provides a checkpoint before `validate:all` | Fold audit into TECH-430/431 rejected — mixes concerns, hides drift |', '{byte-for-byte,audit,phase-n-tail,stanza,across,wired,skill,files,output,tech-430,tech-431,verify,verbatim,template,match,identical,schema_version,stamps,changelog,presence,deviation,patch,inline,source,wiring-review,entry,affected,date,decision,rationale,alternatives,considered}', 'ia/projects/TECH-432.md', '2026-04-18 19:48:41.089214-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (220, 'TECH-423', 'decision_log', '| Date | Decision | Rationale | Alternatives |
|---|---|---|---|
| 2026-04-18 | Default cap = 10_000 (draft) | Round + sizable relative to typical early-game treasury (~5k). Deterministic across legacy saves. | Derive from current treasury × factor — rejected (non-deterministic per-save); tie to city population — rejected (N/A in v3 schema reliably). |', '{stage,phase,migration,branch,legacy,saves,seeds,equal,envelope,normalized,empty,zone,list,pre-existing,save,data,preserved,byte-identical,outside,fields,date,decision,rationale,alternatives,2026-04-18,default,10_000,draft,round,sizable,relative,typical}', 'ia/projects/TECH-423-migrate-save-v3-to-v4.md', '2026-04-18 16:59:25.976108-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (221, 'TECH-424', 'decision_log', '- 2026-04-18 — Deep-copy semantics on both capture and restore (no aliasing either direction). Prevents save payload mutation leaking into runtime state + vice versa.
- 2026-04-18 — Restore trusts persisted `currentMonthRemaining` (no re-derivation from cap × pct). Preserves mid-month remaining after save/load.
- 2026-04-18 — `FindObjectOfType<BudgetAllocationService>` at Save/Load call-sites (not cached on `GameSaveManager`). Matches `GrowthBudgetManager` / `WaterManager` / `RegionalMapManager` pattern already in the same methods; avoids new Inspector field churn.
- 2026-04-18 — Length-mismatch payload → `Default(cap)` fallback, not exception. Keeps load-path robust against hand-edited / corrupted save JSON.', '{stage,phase,bridge,budgetallocationservice,runtime,state,gamesavedata,budgetallocation,adds,capturesavedata,restorefromsavedata,budgetallocationdata,methods,wires,them,gamesavemanager,savegame,pre-write,loadgame,post-migration,ensures,envelope,global,current,month,remaining,survive,save,load,identity,2026-04-18,deep-copy}', 'ia/projects/TECH-424-budget-save-load-roundtrip.md', '2026-04-18 17:07:00.058833-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (222, 'TECH-425', 'decision_log', '- **v3 fixture inline (no JSON file under `Fixtures/`)** — keeps test hermetic + diffable; no I/O dependency in EditMode. (Kickoff 2026-04-18.)
- **Fixture pattern = `TreasuryFloorClampServiceTests` Awake shape, omit `GameNotificationManager`** — null `notificationPanel` NPE on that manager in EditMode; direct reuse of archived TECH-383 lesson.
- **Glossary refs mirror sibling `TreasuryFloorClampService`** — forward-ref `economy-system.md#budget-envelope` (Stage 3.3 authors target) + fallback `docs/zone-s-economy-exploration.md §IP-2`; `economy-system.md` not yet authored — forward-ref pattern already in use for 3 Zone-S rows.', '{stage,phase,closer,lands,editmode,test,classes,service,behavior,save,migration,glossary,rows,budgetallocationservice,ibudgetallocator,index,regen,closes,step,fully,landed,structural,primitives,ready,consumers,bondledgerservice,imaintenancecontributor,zonesservice,fixture,inline,json,file}', 'ia/projects/TECH-425-budget-allocation-tests-glossary.md', '2026-04-18 17:37:27.295422-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (223, 'TECH-430', 'decision_log', '| Date | Decision | Rationale | Alternatives considered |
|------|----------|-----------|------------------------|
| 2026-04-18 | Stanza placed at existing final handoff phase (not new phase) | Matches orchestrator T2.1.1 intent; avoids phase-count drift; keeps lifecycle flow unchanged | New `## Phase N+1 — Self-report` rejected — inflates phase count + breaks existing skill narrative |
| 2026-04-18 | `design-explore` final phase = `Phase 9 — Persist` (no phase labelled "Handoff") | Skill has no explicit "Handoff" phase; Phase 9 — Persist is the terminal phase inside `## Phase sequence` before Gap-analysis-mode variant. Stanza lands there | Placing stanza inside Gap-analysis `Phase 9g — Persist` rejected — duplicates friction capture |
| 2026-04-18 | `{SKILL_NAME}` substituted at paste time; `run_date` `{YYYY-MM-DD}` stays runtime placeholder; `schema_version` pinned to today | Skill name is wiring-time knowable; `run_date` is per-execution; `schema_version` must match template snapshot date for consumer mismatch-warn | Leaving all placeholders literal rejected — would require runtime substitution the skill does not implement |
| 2026-04-18 | `master-plan-extend` already has `## Changelog` (line 351) — do NOT inject duplicate | Section already created by Step 1 bootstrap work; duplication breaks `validate:all` | Re-creating section rejected |', '{append,phase-n-tail,emitter,stanza,verbatim,template,authoring,lifecycle,skills,design-explore,master-plan-new,master-plan-extend,satisfies,stage,exit,ia/skills/skill-train/skill,criterion,authoring-trio,subset,skill,gains,skill_self_report,emission,path,feeding,skill-train,consumer,date,decision,rationale,alternatives,considered}', 'ia/projects/TECH-430.md', '2026-04-18 19:22:14.258914-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
