INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (245, 'TECH-484', 'decision_log', '| Date | Decision | Rationale | Alternatives considered |
|------|----------|-----------|------------------------|
| 2026-04-19 | `jq` primary, sed fallback, drop python3 | `jq` handles escaped quotes → BL-2 resolved; ubiquitous on dev machines; doc as prereq | sed-only (BL-2 risk); keep python3 (fork cost); node (heavier fork) |
| 2026-04-19 | Redirect `jq` stderr to `/dev/null` | Malformed stdin → silent empty `$command_str` → `[ -z … ] && exit 0` guard fires → hook allows (matches today''s python3 `except` behavior); avoids noisy stderr in Claude Code logs | Let jq stderr leak (noisy); explicit `|| echo ""` (redundant with `// ""`) |
| 2026-04-19 | No test fixture for `cs-edit-reminder.sh` | PostToolUse advisory always exits 0 → no security boundary to assert. Fixture scoped to denylist only per NB-4 | Fixture for both (cost without security return) |', '{hook,scripts,bash-denylist,cs-edit-reminder,fork,python3,tool,call,parse,json,stdin,macos,calls,session,seconds,cumulative,wall,latency,convert,pure-shell,primary,handles,json-escaped,quotes,natively,existing,branch,stays,fallback,conservative-deny,behavior,ambiguity}', 'ia/projects/TECH-484-hook-pure-shell-json.md', '2026-04-19 13:22:23.064342-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (246, 'TECH-484', 'lessons_learned', '- …', '{hook,scripts,bash-denylist,cs-edit-reminder,fork,python3,tool,call,parse,json,stdin,macos,calls,session,seconds,cumulative,wall,latency,convert,pure-shell,primary,handles,json-escaped,quotes,natively,existing,branch,stays,fallback,conservative-deny,behavior,ambiguity}', 'ia/projects/TECH-484-hook-pure-shell-json.md', '2026-04-19 13:22:23.181066-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (247, 'TECH-469', 'decision_log', '- **2026-04-19 — Legacy `stage-file/SKILL.md` = dispatcher shim, not tombstone.** `/stage-file` command + `ship-stage` chain reference the skill name directly; preserving it as a thin mode-detection shim avoids rewiring command + chain layers. Full Compress logic moves to sibling; File logic moves to pair. Resolves Open Q1.
- **2026-04-19 — Batch dep verify via `backlog_list`.** Single filter call across union of Stage Depends-on ids; planner stores verified set on each tuple; applier trusts (no re-query). Cuts N × `backlog_issue` → 1 `backlog_list` per Stage.', '{split,monolithic,opus,stage-file-plan,pair-head,sonnet,stage-file-apply,pair-tail,plan-apply,pair,pattern,planner,authors,stage,file,ia/skills/stage-file/skill,plan,structured,tuple,list,entry,task,applier,materializes,yaml,spec,stub,backlog,shared,bundle,loaded,once}', 'ia/projects/TECH-469.md', '2026-04-19 13:37:20.291587-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (248, 'TECH-470', 'decision_log', '| Date | Decision | Rationale | Alternatives considered |
|------|----------|-----------|------------------------|
| 2026-04-19 | Slim applier mirrors `stage-file-apply` Phase 3 structure minus tuple iterator | Single source of truth for Sonnet applier shape; zero new patterns to learn. | Author from scratch — rejected (divergence risk). |
| 2026-04-19 | Tombstone `project-new-plan/` as NEW dir (no source to move) | `ia/skills/project-new-plan/` does not exist in tree — only monolithic `ia/skills/project-new/`. | Move `ia/skills/project-new/` whole — rejected (downstream T7.8 still repoints via it). |
| 2026-04-19 | Leave seam #3 row in `plan-apply-pair-contract.md` | Backlog notes assign seam #3 row drop to T7.11 / TECH-478 (`drop project-new-plan→project-new-apply seam entry`). | Drop seam row here — rejected (scope creep across task boundary). |
| 2026-04-19 | 5-phase applier (no task-table flip phase) | Single-issue path — no orchestrator/master-plan task row to update. Differs from `stage-file-apply` 6-phase shape (drops its Phase 5). | 6-phase parity — rejected (dead phase). |', '{collapse,single-issue,flow,drop,project-new,plan,opus,pair-head,pair,author,slim,sonnet,reads,args,directly,/project-new,ia/skills/project-new-apply/skill,command,materializes,reserve-id,ia/backlog/,yaml,ia/projects/,stub,materialize-backlog,validate,dead-project-specs,hands,plan-author,contract,authored,tech-478}', 'ia/projects/TECH-470.md', '2026-04-19 13:47:53.959356-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (249, 'TECH-471', 'decision_log', '- 2026-04-19 — opus-audit scope = Stage-scoped bulk synthesis, NOT per-Task. Rationale: one Opus pass over shared Stage MCP bundle minimizes context reload + produces consistent voice across N paragraphs. Per-Task audit regression = forbidden per R10 (never regress bulk → per-Task).
- 2026-04-19 — opus-code-review stays per-Task. Rationale: defect-detection latency couples tight to `/verify-loop` cycle; bulk code-review flagged as rev 4 candidate S8 only.
- 2026-04-19 — code-fix-apply retry bound = 1 (2 total attempts). Rationale: matches existing pair-tail retry convention; second fail = escalate to Opus re-plan, do not loop.
- 2026-04-19 — Pair-contract seam #5 row edit deferred to T7.11. Rationale: row rewrite couples to `plan-author` Stage-end fold + `stage-closeout-plan` landing; editing here creates stale state mid-Stage.', '{land,three,audit-chain,skills,opus-audit,opus,stage-scoped,bulk,pass,writes,audit,paragraphs,feeds,stage-closeout-plan,opus-code-review,per-task,pair-head,minor,critical,code,plan,code-fix-apply,sonnet,pair-tail,applies,tuples,re-enters,/verify-loop,retry,bound,2026-04-19,scope}', 'ia/projects/TECH-471.md', '2026-04-19 13:59:02.524687-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (250, 'TECH-472', 'decision_log', '- 2026-04-19 — Adopt tombstone pattern from `ia/skills/_retired/project-new-plan/` (frontmatter `loaded_by: none` + `purpose` redirect + H1 "X — RETIRED" + prose block). Consistent w/ prior Stage 7 retirements.
- 2026-04-19 — `git mv` (not `cp` + `rm`) preserves history for both SKILL.md and CHANGELOG.md files under close skill.
- 2026-04-19 — Spec-enrich not authored; canonical-term enforcement folded into bulk `plan-author` Opus author-time pass per rev 3 exploration extension (shared Stage MCP bundle carries glossary snippets).', '{retirement-only,task,move,tombstone,redirect,headers,spec-enrich,never,authored,canonical-term,enforcement,absorbed,bulk,plan-author,tech-478,ia/skills/project-spec-kickoff/,ia/skills/project-spec-close/,ia/skills/_retired/,skill,authoring,here,2026-04-19,adopt,pattern,ia/skills/_retired/project-new-plan/,frontmatter,loaded_by,none,purpose,retired,prose,block}', 'ia/projects/TECH-472.md', '2026-04-19 14:08:42.788258-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (253, 'TECH-503', 'decision_log', '| Date | Decision | Rationale | Alternatives considered |
|------|----------|-----------|------------------------|
| 2026-04-19 | Single concatenated block per agent body (option (a)) | Avoids F6 20-block lookback risk as conversation grows; R4 locked option (a) for stable prefix | Option (b) multi-block — forbidden per §3 + §4 R4 |
| 2026-04-19 | 1h TTL both tiers | R3 walkthrough shows 5m expires mid-Stage at N=4 fan-out; 1h covers full Stage lifecycle with margin | 5m default — rejected per F4 regression + R3 |
| 2026-04-19 | Tier 1 = rules + glossary preamble only (NOT full glossary) | Full glossary is Tier 2 scope (per-Stage subset via `glossary_discover`); Tier 1 stays cross-Stage stable — edits to full glossary rows should NOT cascade-invalidate Tier 1 | Include full glossary — regresses F5 cascade surface |
| 2026-04-19 | CI sizing gate (R2) vs runtime warning | Silent no-cache is already billed by the time runtime sees it; catch at CI | Runtime-only assertion — rejected |
| 2026-04-19 | Validator opt-in (skip agents without `cache_control`) | Not every agent needs Tier 1 prefix (e.g. Sonnet executors with spec-local context); forcing blanket emission wastes writes | Mandatory emission — regresses F3 stagger economics |
| 2026-04-19 | Glossary preamble slice = header + authorship note + index table only | Per Q4 resolution: full glossary rows are Tier 2 scope; preamble slice keeps Tier 1 cross-Stage stable and avoids F5 cascade on per-term edits | Include full glossary — regresses F5 cascade surface |
| 2026-04-19 | Measured block size: 23,629 bytes (rules only) + 2,088 bytes (preamble file) = 25,717 bytes total → ~6,429 tokens | Clears Opus 4.7 F2 floor (4,096) by ×1.57; Sonnet 4.6 floor (1,024) by ×6.3 | N/A — measurement only |', '{land,tier,stable,cross-stage,cache,block,sizing,gate,author,rules,-concat,target,single,concatenated,option,docs/prompt-caching-mechanics,ia/skills/_preamble/stable-block,f6/r4,compliant,emit,messages,content,cache_control,type,ephemeral,explicit-ttl,rule,agent,bodies,pair-seam,agents,plan-reviewer}', 'ia/projects/TECH-503.md', '2026-04-19 22:02:37.381643-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (254, 'TECH-503', 'lessons_learned', '- …', '{land,tier,stable,cross-stage,cache,block,sizing,gate,author,rules,-concat,target,single,concatenated,option,docs/prompt-caching-mechanics,ia/skills/_preamble/stable-block,f6/r4,compliant,emit,messages,content,cache_control,type,ephemeral,explicit-ttl,rule,agent,bodies,pair-seam,agents,plan-reviewer}', 'ia/projects/TECH-503.md', '2026-04-19 22:02:37.442832-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (255, 'TECH-504', 'decision_log', '| Date | Decision | Rationale | Alternatives considered |
|------|----------|-----------|------------------------|
| 2026-04-19 | Single Stage-start bundle | Avoids duplicate MCP round-trips per Task | Per-Task bundle (wasteful) |
| 2026-04-19 | Phase N token-floor = log-and-continue | T10.2 CI gate is hard-fail authority; runtime assert is advisory safety net — avoids blocking lifecycle on transient MCP under-fill | Hard-fail runtime (blocks Stage), silent (no signal) |
| 2026-04-19 | Phase N location = inside `domain-context-load` | Single callsite; all 8+ lifecycle callers inherit cache block automatically | Per-caller concat (duplicates contract) |', '{edit,phase,final,concat,assembling,glossary,subset,spec_sections,invariants_summary,aggregator,single,cache_control,ephemeral,content,block,ia/skills/domain-context-load/skill,update,stage-file-plan,skill,invoke,domain-context-load,exactly,once,stage,ia/rules/plan-apply-pair-contract,cite,tier,bundle,reuse,contract,date,decision}', 'ia/projects/TECH-504.md', '2026-04-19 22:12:14.89314-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (256, 'TECH-504', 'lessons_learned', '- …', '{edit,phase,final,concat,assembling,glossary,subset,spec_sections,invariants_summary,aggregator,single,cache_control,ephemeral,content,block,ia/skills/domain-context-load/skill,update,stage-file-plan,skill,invoke,domain-context-load,exactly,once,stage,ia/rules/plan-apply-pair-contract,cite,tier,bundle,reuse,contract,date,decision}', 'ia/projects/TECH-504.md', '2026-04-19 22:12:14.906781-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (257, 'TECH-505', 'decision_log', '| Date | Decision | Rationale | Alternatives considered |
|------|----------|-----------|------------------------|
| 2026-04-19 | B2 atomic commit | Prevents mid-flight ordering breakage (amendment 3) | Split commits |
| 2026-04-20 | Uniformity target = "pair-head OR pair-tail within same seam", not "all agents" | Pair-tails (Sonnet appliers) legitimately need narrower tools (no MCP router / glossary); pair-heads (Opus) need full research toolkit. Enforcing identical list across roles would bloat appliers. | Single global tools list across every agent |
| 2026-04-20 | Validator groups by pair-seam role (head vs tail), asserts uniformity within role across seams | Detects drift (e.g., one planner missing `glossary_lookup`) without collapsing head/tail distinction | Group by pair pair-id; group by model |', '{edit,plan-author,opus-audit,phase,sequential-dispatch,guardrail,concurrent,opus,fan-out,stage-scoped,bulk,enforce,tool-allowlist,uniformity,across,pair-seam,agent,bodies,author,validate-agent-tools-uniformity,wired,validate,retire,findings,gate,atomically,output,gets,inline,sub-section,same,commit}', 'ia/projects/TECH-505.md', '2026-04-20 06:02:41.810695-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (258, 'TECH-505', 'lessons_learned', '- …', '{edit,plan-author,opus-audit,phase,sequential-dispatch,guardrail,concurrent,opus,fan-out,stage-scoped,bulk,enforce,tool-allowlist,uniformity,across,pair-seam,agent,bodies,author,validate-agent-tools-uniformity,wired,validate,retire,findings,gate,atomically,output,gets,inline,sub-section,same,commit}', 'ia/projects/TECH-505.md', '2026-04-20 06:02:41.860541-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (259, 'TECH-518', 'decision_log', '| Date | Decision | Rationale | Alternatives considered |
|------|----------|-----------|------------------------|
| 2026-04-19 | Heuristic set = 6 (cohesion, verify overlap, LOC, DAG, invariant density, compile-break). | Covers observed failure modes in sibling findings doc. | Start w/ 3 (cohesion + LOC + DAG) — rejected as under-signaled. |
| 2026-04-19 | Gate is LLM-prompt heuristic, not CI check. | Task cluster scope is semantic; threshold fuzziness better than false-positive CI failure. | CI validator (`validate-stage-sizing.ts`) — rejected as premature; revisit post dry-run. |
| 2026-04-20 | Dry-run 1 — mcp-lifecycle-tools Stage 6 (T6.1–T6.4, 4 tasks): H1=WARN(3 subsystems), H2–H6=PASS. Outcome: PASS (≤1 WARN). Recurse: 0. Reauthor cost: 0. | Stage cohesion slightly wide (ia/skills + tools/scripts + tools/mcp-ia-server) but LOC/DAG/invariant all clean; WARN does not trigger recurse. Gate calibrated correctly. | N/A — PASS path. |
| 2026-04-20 | Dry-run 2 — mcp-lifecycle-tools Stage 10 (T10.1–T10.4, 4 tasks): H1–H4=PASS, H5=WARN(T10.1+T10.2 share invariant #12 path guard), H6=PASS. Outcome: PASS (≤1 WARN). Recurse: 0. Reauthor cost: 0. | TypeScript tooling Stage; both tasks share invariant #12 (ia/projects/ path validation) as a coincident best-practice, not a conflict — WARN correctly signals coupling without blocking. | N/A — PASS path. |
| 2026-04-20 | Dry-run 3 — lifecycle-refactor Stage 10 T10.5–T10.8 (4 tasks): H1=WARN(ia/skills + .claude/agents + docs), H2–H6=PASS. Outcome: PASS (≤1 WARN). Recurse: 0. Reauthor cost: 0. | IA/doc-only Stage; 3 subsystems but LOC budget well under 800, no Path B, no invariant coupling, no C# mutations. WARN acceptable; thresholds hold for doc-heavy Stages. | N/A — PASS path. |
| 2026-04-20 | Dry-run calibration note: all 3 test Stages PASS (1 WARN each on H1 or H5). Thresholds appear correct for doc/IA-only Stages. H1 FAIL threshold (≥4 subsystems) not triggered; next empirical gap: apply gate to a runtime C# Stage with mixed Path A/B to stress H1+H2+H6 simultaneously. Defer to TECH-519 empirical data. | Dry-run set covers IA/tooling surface only (per §2.2 non-goal 4). C# Stage stress-test deferred. | N/A. |', '{gate,stage,decomposition,bulk-verify,bulk-code-review,feasibility,task,cluster,rule,layers,analytic,heuristics,existing,cardinality,hard,ia/rules/stage-sizing-gate,soft,ia/rules/project-hierarchy,failure,recurse-split,reauthor,context,docs/stage-scoped-verify-review-findings,authored,same,turn,sibling,stage-scoped,verify/review,expansion,work,distinct}', 'ia/projects/TECH-518.md', '2026-04-20 06:46:32.517995-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (260, 'TECH-518', 'lessons_learned', '- …', '{gate,stage,decomposition,bulk-verify,bulk-code-review,feasibility,task,cluster,rule,layers,analytic,heuristics,existing,cardinality,hard,ia/rules/stage-sizing-gate,soft,ia/rules/project-hierarchy,failure,recurse-split,reauthor,context,docs/stage-scoped-verify-review-findings,authored,same,turn,sibling,stage-scoped,verify/review,expansion,work,distinct}', 'ia/projects/TECH-518.md', '2026-04-20 06:46:32.555395-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (265, 'TECH-702', 'decision_log', '| Date | Decision | Rationale | Alternatives considered |
|------|----------|-----------|------------------------|
| 2026-04-23 | `content_h ∈ [32, 36]` (±2 of House1-64''s 35) | Catches any drift ≥3 px while tolerating variant permutation | Exact match `content_h == 35` — rejected, variant permutation alters h slightly |
| 2026-04-23 | `y1 == 48` exact, no tolerance | Diamond bottom is invariant; variant cannot shift it | `46 <= y1 <= 50` — rejected, masks pivot regressions |', '{replace,loose,bound,test_scale_calibration,tight,house1-64,envelope,content_h,closes,regression,hole,original,pivot,ship,range,wide,enough,swallow,scale,drift,date,decision,rationale,alternatives,considered,------,----------,-----------,------------------------,2026-04-23,catches,tolerating}', 'ia/projects/TECH-702.md', '2026-04-23 13:17:18.290758-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (266, 'TECH-702', 'lessons_learned', '- Regression bounds should be as tight as the reference envelope; +3/−3 tolerance on an invariant (diamond bottom) lets bugs ride for weeks.', '{replace,loose,bound,test_scale_calibration,tight,house1-64,envelope,content_h,closes,regression,hole,original,pivot,ship,range,wide,enough,swallow,scale,drift,date,decision,rationale,alternatives,considered,------,----------,-----------,------------------------,2026-04-23,catches,tolerating}', 'ia/projects/TECH-702.md', '2026-04-23 13:17:18.30881-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (267, 'TECH-703', 'decision_log', '| Date | Decision | Rationale | Alternatives considered |
|------|----------|-----------|------------------------|
| 2026-04-23 | Parametrize over `pytest.mark.parametrize` with IDs derived from spec stem | Stable CI output; new specs auto-covered | Looped assertions inside one test function — rejected, single failure masks rest |
| 2026-04-23 | Filter out sloped / non-1×1 specs inside helper | Stage 6.1 scope is flat 1×1 only per handoff acceptance criteria | Assert universally — rejected, slope variants have different bbox |', '{parametrized,pytest,case,test_render_integration,iterates,every,live,yaml,building_residential_small,building_residential_light_,asserts,renders,bbox,exactly,closes,specs/,hole,tech-702,locks,canonical,spec,future,specs,silently,drift,date,decision,rationale,alternatives,considered,------,----------}', 'ia/projects/TECH-703.md', '2026-04-23 13:17:18.528832-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
INSERT INTO public.ia_project_spec_journal VALUES (268, 'TECH-703', 'lessons_learned', '- Parametrize regression tests over `specs/*.yaml` so new specs inherit coverage automatically; avoids the silent-drift pattern where each new YAML needs a hand-written test.', '{parametrized,pytest,case,test_render_integration,iterates,every,live,yaml,building_residential_small,building_residential_light_,asserts,renders,bbox,exactly,closes,specs/,hole,tech-702,locks,canonical,spec,future,specs,silently,drift,date,decision,rationale,alternatives,considered,------,----------}', 'ia/projects/TECH-703.md', '2026-04-23 13:17:18.591551-04', NULL, DEFAULT);
